### **2Ô∏è‚É£ Passing Parameters to FastCGI (PHP Example)**

---

#### **üîπ Step 1: Install PHP-FPM**
```sh
sudo apt update
sudo apt install php-fpm
```

---

#### **üîπ Step 2: Create a PHP File (`/var/www/html/index.php`)**
```php
<?php
if (isset($_SERVER['HTTP_X_CUSTOM_PARAM'])) {
    echo "PHP received: " . $_SERVER['HTTP_X_CUSTOM_PARAM'];
} else {
    echo "No param received!";
}
?>
```

---

#### **üîπ Step 3: Configure Nginx to Pass Custom Parameter to FastCGI**
Edit your Nginx configuration (`/etc/nginx/sites-available/default`):
```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name _;

    root /var/www/html;
    index index.php;

    location ~ \.php$ {
        include fastcgi_params;
        fastcgi_pass unix:/run/php/php8.1-fpm.sock;
        fastcgi_param X-Custom-Param "Hello PHP from Nginx!";
        fastcgi_param SCRIPT_FILENAME $document_root$fastcgi_script_name;
    }
}
```

---

#### **üîπ Step 4: Restart PHP-FPM and Nginx**
```sh
sudo systemctl restart php8.1-fpm nginx
```

---

#### **üîπ Step 5: Test with Curl**
```sh
curl -H "X-Custom-Param: TestValue" http://localhost/index.php
```
Expected output:
```
PHP received: TestValue
```

---

### **üìå Summary**
- **Flask with uWSGI** ‚Üí Pass parameters using `uwsgi_param`  
- **PHP with FastCGI** ‚Üí Pass parameters using `fastcgi_param`  

‚úÖ Now you can pass parameters dynamically from Nginx to Flask and PHP! üöÄ Let me know if you need modifications.